With the help of a broad selection of visual materials, the various characters and pictorial types that are prevalent in Christian art will be examined. The entire compositions as well as the individual details will be examined; this will be carried out in the broader context of Christian culture as well as the narrower framework of sacred space and specific pictorial types.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview of the basic signs and symbols in Christian art and thereby create the preconditions for understanding and interpreting Christian art.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student that completes the course: - will know the most prevalent pictorial types and characters in Christian art;  - will be familiar with the Bible stories most often used in Christian art;    - will understand and be able to interpret works of Christian art;  - will be able to place examples of Christian art in their cultural context;  - will know the most important Christian symbols;  - will know how to interpret the most important signs and symbols of Christian art.
